editorialNotes.standard: Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivated—and Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new ‘dos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

ios.subtitle: Create to show what you know!

editorialNotes.standard: We’ve played so many games that we feel like we could create our own—and now we can, all without coding classes or complex tutorials. With this ingenious educational app, it's easy to become a designer. Imagination rules as you build characters, worlds and stories for one-of-a-kind games meant to be saved, shared and—of course—played.

name: Word Wizard for Kids School Ed

editorialNotes.standard: What are those towers that touch the sky? Tinybop’s awesome sandbox teaches kids the fun way—by letting them build, watch, and play. As they add floors and test the effects of plumbing problems and earthquakes, they're actually learning basic design and engineering principles. Amazing details abound—from all the busy little inhabitants to the full-blown skyline you can make.

name: Cosmolander - Missions in the Solar System

editorialNotes.standard: We’re having Jupiter-sized fun with this educational spin around the solar system. Cosmolander brings fascinating facts about the planets to life with colorful artwork and animated quizzes that play like video games. Best of all, there’s a wealth of real scientific information to be discovered, so the entire family can share in learning more about our cosmic backyard.
